hpnicfRCPMIB.name: hpnicfRCPMIB
hpnicfRCPMIB.description: The MIB module is used for managing RCP protocol server.

hpnicfRCPServerEnableStatus.name: hpnicfRCPServerEnableStatus
hpnicfRCPServerEnableStatus.description: This attribute controls the system wide operation of RCP server. The value TRUE means that the RCP server is enabled. The value FALSE means that the RCP server is disabled.

hpnicfRCPConnTimeout.name: hpnicfRCPConnTimeout
hpnicfRCPConnTimeout.description: Specifies the maximum time in seconds that a RCP client connection is idle.

hpnicfRCPRuleTimeout.name: hpnicfRCPRuleTimeout
hpnicfRCPRuleTimeout.description: Specifies the time in seconds before a RCP rule is aged out. If its value is 0, it indicates RCP rule will not be aged out.

hpnicfRCPServerMaxConn.name: hpnicfRCPServerMaxConn
hpnicfRCPServerMaxConn.description: Specifies the maximum number of clients that permitted to connect with RCP server at the same time.

hpnicfRCPServerCurConn.name: hpnicfRCPServerCurConn
hpnicfRCPServerCurConn.description: The current actual number of clients that connecting with RCP server.

hpnicfRCPConnTimeoutMaxValue.name: hpnicfRCPConnTimeoutMaxValue
hpnicfRCPConnTimeoutMaxValue.description: Specifies the maximum value of hpnicfRCPConnTimeout.

hpnicfRCPRuleTimeoutMaxValue.name: hpnicfRCPRuleTimeoutMaxValue
hpnicfRCPRuleTimeoutMaxValue.description: Specifies the maximum value of hpnicfRCPRuleTimeout.

hpnicfRCPServerMaxConnMaxValue.name: hpnicfRCPServerMaxConnMaxValue
hpnicfRCPServerMaxConnMaxValue.description: Specifies the maximum value of hpnicfRCPServerMaxConn.

hpnicfRCPBalanceGroupIdMinValue.name: hpnicfRCPBalanceGroupIdMinValue
hpnicfRCPBalanceGroupIdMinValue.description: Specifies the minimum value of balance group identity.

hpnicfRCPBalanceGroupIdMaxValue.name: hpnicfRCPBalanceGroupIdMaxValue
hpnicfRCPBalanceGroupIdMaxValue.description: Specifies the maximum value of balance group identity.

hpnicfRCPTotalUsers.name: hpnicfRCPTotalUsers
hpnicfRCPTotalUsers.description: Specifies the total number of RCP user.

hpnicfRCPTotalClientIPs.name: hpnicfRCPTotalClientIPs
hpnicfRCPTotalClientIPs.description: Specifies the total number of RCP client IP.

hpnicfRCPUserPassword.name: hpnicfRCPUserPassword
hpnicfRCPUserPassword.description: The password of RCP user. It is invisible to users and displayed as '***'.

hpnicfRCPUserRedirectInterface.name: hpnicfRCPUserRedirectInterface
hpnicfRCPUserRedirectInterface.description: The redirect interface index of RCP user. The RCP rule assigned by the user can be associated with the redirect interface. If the redirect interface is invalid, its value is set to be 0.

hpnicfRCPUserRedirectBalanceGroup.name: hpnicfRCPUserRedirectBalanceGroup
hpnicfRCPUserRedirectBalanceGroup.description: The redirect balance group identity of RCP user. The RCP rule assigned by the user can be associated with the redirect balance group. If the balance group is invalid, its value is set to be 0.

hpnicfRCPUserRowStatus.name: hpnicfRCPUserRowStatus
hpnicfRCPUserRowStatus.description: This manages the creation and deletion of rows, and shows the current status of the indexed user name. This object has the following values. active(1) The indexed user name is configured on the device. notInService(2) Not Supported. notReady(3) Not Supported. createAndGo(4) Create a new user. createAndWait(5) Not Supported. destroy(6) Delete this entry. The associated entry can be modified when the value of hpnicfRCPUserRowStatus is active(1). When deleting an inexistence entry, return noError.

hpnicfRCPClientIPType.name: hpnicfRCPClientIPType
hpnicfRCPClientIPType.description: The IP address type (IPv4 or IPv6) of RCP client.

hpnicfRCPClientIP.name: hpnicfRCPClientIP
hpnicfRCPClientIP.description: The IP address of RCP client.

hpnicfRCPClientIPRowStatus.name: hpnicfRCPClientIPRowStatus
hpnicfRCPClientIPRowStatus.description: This manages the creation and deletion or rows, and shows the current status of the indexed client IP address. This object has the following values. active(1) The indexed client IP is configured on the device. notInService(2) Not Supported. notReady(3) Not Supported. createAndGo(4) Create a new client IP. createAndWait(5) Not Supported. destroy(6) Delete this entry. The associated entry can be modified when the value of hpnicfRCPClientIPRowStatus is active(1). When deleting an inexistence entry, return noError.

hpnicfRCPSessionClientIPType.name: hpnicfRCPSessionClientIPType
hpnicfRCPSessionClientIPType.description: The IP address type (IPv4 or IPv6) of RCP client.

hpnicfRCPSessionRunningStatus.name: hpnicfRCPSessionRunningStatus
hpnicfRCPSessionRunningStatus.description: RCP server running status. It is one of the following status: connected: The connection is established and the RCP client is waiting for authentication. operational: The RCP client is authenticated and the server is ready for rule configuration request.
